# Shiba Studio environment overrides — copy to .env.local and fill in.
# .env.local is gitignored, so your secrets stay on your machine.

# --- Google Drive sign-in (optional: makes Drive zero-setup for every user) ---
# Create ONE OAuth client in Google Cloud Console:
#   APIs & Services → Credentials → Create OAuth client ID → Web application
#   Authorized redirect URI: http://localhost:3000/api/google-oauth/callback
#   (also enable the Google Drive API for the project)
# Paste the client's ID and secret below. When set, the Capabilities → Google
# Drive card shows "Sign in with Google" with no per-user setup — users just
# sign in and approve. Leave blank to have each user add their own client under
# the card's Advanced section.
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=

# --- Optional runtime overrides (see docs/configuration.md) ---
# SHIBA_DATA_DIR=      # where all runtime data lives (default ~/.shiba-studio/data)
# SHIBA_PROJECT_ROOT=  # source/workspace root if the process starts elsewhere
# SHIBA_SECRET_KEY_FILE= # persistent key-file path (Docker uses /data/shiba-studio.key)
# SHIBA_SECRET_KEY=    # 64 hex chars — AES key for headless installs (overrides the key file)
# SHIBA_GIT_COMMIT=    # commit shown in the footer for non-git installs

# --- Slim install: skip the ~150 MB Chromium download ---
# Set before `npm install` if you'll never use browser automation / the sub-browser.
# Fetch Chromium later with: npx puppeteer browsers install chrome-headless-shell
# PUPPETEER_SKIP_DOWNLOAD=1

# --- Reach the app by name on the network (mDNS / Bonjour) ---
# The app advertises http://shiba.local:3000 automatically. Rename or disable:
# SHIBA_MDNS_HOST=shiba.local   # comma-separated for several names; a bare label gets ".local" appended
# SHIBA_MDNS=off               # disable mDNS advertising entirely
# (dev:lan / start:lan advertise the LAN IP so other devices can reach it by name)
# Bare http://shiba.local (port 80) redirects to the app port so you can skip typing it:
# SHIBA_PORT80=off             # disable the port-80 redirect (bare shiba.local won't forward)
# SHIBA_APP_PORT=3000          # port the redirect targets (defaults to PORT, else 3000)
